parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt locks up
the seat belt does not return to its normal position
the seat belt has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to restrain the driver or passenger in case of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dealer Refusal to Honor Recall Notice
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dealer's refusal to honor the recall notice can lead to the continued use of a faulty seat belt system, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The dealer refuses to repair or replace the faulty seat belt system
despite the presence of a recall notice
leaving the vehicle owner with a safety risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturer's refusal to admit the defect can lead to a lack of accountability and a failure to provide a timely and effective solution, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The manufacturer denies the existence of a defect or refuses to take responsibility for the faulty seat belt system
leaving vehicle owners with a safety risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling line can cause a fire, leading to a total loss of the vehicle, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the wheel well
transmission fluid leaking onto the wheel and brake pads
strange odor
flames
transmission coolant line rupture
transmission fluid spraying up into the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle unable to stop
brake pedal with no response
transmission on fire within the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to properly notify vehicle owners of recalls can lead to a lack of awareness about potential safety issues, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle owners unaware of recalls
despite matching recall criteria
being given the runaround by the manufacturer and dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Idling Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and idling issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The constant stalling can also cause damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: The "Service Engine Soon" light turns on
the engine idles high
the engine goes into a "super idle" mode
the vehicle stalls frequently
power drain
battery indicator shoots up
lights dim
heater goes out
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of oil pressure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: The engine loses all oil pressure at speeds of 15 to 25mph until driving straight again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine components can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: Headbolt failure
fuel pump failure
thermostat failure
engine fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various systems to fail, leading to safety concerns and inconvenience.
symptoms: The air conditioner never worked
the window controllers had to be replaced
the battery had to be replaced twice
the alternator had to be replaced once
the rear wiper's solvent system does not work
the front wipers will not work occasionally
the horn does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to inconvenience and potential safety concerns.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is off by 1/4 tank
reading 1/4 tank of gas left when the tank is actually empty.
